The paper focuses on image retrieval using deep learning and quantization techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to learning deep quantization models, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of similarity triplets and back-propagation, which are common techniques in information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
